**Title:** COM – BadgeLife Community – SAINTCON

**Website:** [saintcon.org](https://saintcon.org)

**Overview:**
The BadgeLife Community is a part of the SAINTCON event, which celebrates the world of badges and their associated culture. The community is supported by various contributors, including Compukidmike, Redactd, Klipper, V0rtex, Mike's Wife, and BP. 

**Description:**
- Badgelife is described as "the best life," inviting participants to explore the intriguing universe of badges.
- There is mention of an old engineering drawing related to the Klippy-Net Wrist Communicator, suggesting involvement in projects or reverse engineering aspects.
- Participants are encouraged to check out additional resources and details on GitHub, including KiCad templates: [GitHub Repository](https://github.com/compukidmike/Saintcon2024).

**FAQ Highlights:**
- **Badge Information:** Limited information is available before the conference; participants can refer to GitHub for details.
- **Collaborations and Integrations:** There are no guarantees for supporting unique integrations due to resource constraints.
- **General Questions:** Includes humorous responses about team dynamics and preferences.

**Hours of Operation:**
- **Monday:** Expo Closed
- **Tuesday:** 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday:** 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Thursday:** 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Friday:** 9:00 AM – 11:00 AM

**MiniBadge and Community Engagement:**
- A MiniBadge will be available, with details accessible at the community booth during the event.
- Desktop wallpaper for the community is also available for download.

